s\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also the Beijing one in 2008.pic.twitter.com/594QBgX2Fz  The London ceremony was great but to be fair so is this.\", \"from\": 3562, \"to\": 3675, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Very Stylish and Paris looks beautiful, even in the rain.#OpeningCeremony  The event saw a total of 85 boats carry the team delegations on a six-kilometre journey through the centre of Paris, with more than 300,000 spectators lining the banks of the river.\", \"from\": 3676, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3693, \"end\": 3698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.674617773732437e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3861, \"end\": 3866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.674617773732437e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lady Gaga was the first singer to perform at the opening ceremony and\\u00a0surprised viewers by singing in French\\u00a0during her performance, which saw her deliver a burlesque take on the French classic Mon Truc En Plume.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3934, \"end\": 3943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 4036, \"end\": 4042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9983524697027528, \"rank\": 0.0014874275387359683, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4113, \"end\": 4127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 38-year-old emerged from a plume of pink feathers as she sang alongside a group of dancers while wearing a black bodice with a detachable black and pink ruffled skirt.\", \"from\": 4148, \"to\": 4319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Poker Face singer performed next to the River Seine, near the Notre Dame cathedral, during what is the first-ever opening ceremony to be staged outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 4321, \"to\": 4487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4325, \"end\": 4335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poker_Face_(song)\", \"score\": 0.9951564544582866, \"rank\": 0.0048360846314775005, \"text\": \"Poker Face\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poker_Face_(song)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poker_Face_(song)\"}, {\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following a sequence paying homage to the historical epic, French heavy metal band Gojira performed at the Conciergerie, a former courthouse and prison in the city.\", \"from\": 4489, \"to\": 4653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4548, \"end\": 4554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9983524697027528, \"rank\": 0.0014874275387359683, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4572, \"end\": 4578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4920290158066575e-40, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 4596, \"end\": 4608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.754096281765522e-33, \"text\": \"Conciergerie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the other performers was French-Malian singer Aya Nakamura, who sang while dressed in a golden dress paired with gladiator boots and gold jewellery.\", \"from\": 4655, \"to\": 4809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4707, \"end\": 4719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The celebrations were met with heavy rain with artists including pianist Alexandre Kantorow, braving heavy showers during their performances.\", \"from\": 4811, \"to\": 4952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4884, \"end\": 4902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexandre Kantorow\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event concluded with an unforgettable performance by Celine Dion, her first since revealing she is living with stiff person syndrome.\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 5091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5011, \"end\": 5022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4041411655696832e-65, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The My Heart Will Go On pop legend sang Edith Piaf's L'Hymne A L'Amour on the first stage of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 5093, \"to\": 5203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5133, \"end\": 5143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"score\": 0.9999999912251951, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Edith Piaf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She appeared dressed in a beaded silver gown with a high neckline and seemed emotional as she came to the climax of the song.\", \"from\": 5205, \"to\": 5330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The London 2012 opening ceremony, meanwhile, was an entire spectacle entitled\\u00a0Isles of Wonder\\u00a0and directed by\\u00a0Academy Award-winning Trainspotting director\\u00a0Danny Boyle.\", \"from\": 5332, \"to\": 5499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5336, \"end\": 5364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 opening ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 5487, \"end\": 5498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Danny Boyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to the Queen, 007 and the Spice Girls, fans were enraptured by comedian Rowan Atkinson's performance as Mr Bean with the London Symphony Orchestra.\", \"from\": 5501, \"to\": 5660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5585, \"end\": 5599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowan_Atkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rowan Atkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowan_Atkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowan_Atkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 5617, \"end\": 5624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7087542739869217e-51, \"text\": \"Mr Bean\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\"}, {\"begin\": 5634, \"end\": 5659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Symphony_Orchestra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London Symphony Orchestra\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Symphony_Orchestra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Symphony_Orchestra\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show won universal critical acclaim including from French newspaper Le Figaro which said it 'reminded a billion viewers of the best contributions that Britain has given to the world for over a century: its sense of humour, its music, and of course sport.'\", \"from\": 5662, \"to\": 5921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5717, \"end\": 5723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9983524697027528, \"rank\": 0.0014874275387359683, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5817, \"end\": 5824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999998881322, \"rank\": 1.1185586568910976e-10, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In The Guardian, Richard Boyle said: 'For four years, following Beijing was thought to be the most thankless task in show business.\", \"from\": 5923, \"to\": 6054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5926, \"end\": 5938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Guardian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.583080850517364e-39, \"text\": \"The Guardian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Guardian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Guardian\"}, {\"begin\": 5940, \"end\": 5953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Boyle,_1st_Earl_of_Cork\", \"score\": 0.47910737244604007, \"rank\": 0.8139534883721203, \"text\": \"Richard Boyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Boyle,_1st_Earl_of_Cork\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Boyle,_1st_Earl_of_Cork\"}, {\"begin\": 5987, \"end\": 5994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9647406951318748, \"rank\": 0.03654796054821108, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Danny Boyle made it happen.\", \"from\": 6055, \"to\": 6082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6055, \"end\": 6066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Danny Boyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He made the stadium seem bigger than it is, as big as the world.\", \"from\": 6083, \"to\": 6147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He gave a party, full of jokes and warmth and noise and drama, and he got the Olympics started.'\", \"from\": 6148, \"to\": 6244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony broke BBC records at the time, and was watched by a peak audience of just under 27m - making it the most watched broadcast of 2012.\", \"from\": 6246, \"to\": 6398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6273, \"end\": 6276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.7717591510378222, \"rank\": 0.2957410335277996, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also drew an average audience of 40.7 million people in the US, which topped the previous ratings record for a summer sports game of 39.8 million for the Atlanta Games in 1996.\", \"from\": 6400, \"to\": 6579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6463, \"end\": 6465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.8646008819071334, \"rank\": 0.15186895601965322, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Struggling with thinning or dull hair?\", \"from\": 6581, \"to\": 6619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Experts say the real issue starts at your scalp  Mother's Day gifts for new mums and mums\\u2011to\\u2011be under \\u00a350  The oral\\u2011care gadget making waves thanks to its powerful clean  Dunelm's new outdoor collection will get your garden spring-ready - from just \\u00a33  The exact blush Margot Robbie wore in Wuthering Heights and best budget alternatives  The Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony is available to watch on BBC iPlayer.\", \"from\": 6620, \"to\": 7032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6791, \"end\": 6797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durham_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.221755459542492e-13,